890005_Thank you for using Photos. Photos (the \"App\" or \"Photos\") is a product that provides you with an immersive experience of browsing photos and videos and allows you to intelligently manage and easily edit your photos and videos.

890702_This Photos Privacy Notice (this \"Privacy Notice\") explains what personal information we collect from you during your use of Photos, how and why do so, your rights to your personal information, and the security measures we use to protect your personal information.

890701_Before using Photos, please carefully read this Privacy Notice, with special attention to the terms highlighted in bold, to understand our practices regarding personal information protection. If you do not agree to this Privacy Notice, we may not be able to provide you with services related to Photos. By tapping \"Agree\", you acknowledge that you clearly and fully understand our collection and use of your personal information as described below.
890002_1. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information

890001_We collect personal information in order to operate more efficiently and provide you with an optimal user experience. We collect personal information about you in three primary ways: (1) directly from you; (2) automatically from your use of Photos; and/or (3) from third parties.

890000_The information we collect depends on the product features you use, the environment in which you interact with us, and the choices you make, including your privacy settings and the products and features you use.

889999_Please note that if the following clauses do not explicitly state that your relevant information will be uploaded to our server, then the information is only stored, collected, and processed locally on your device. This is to clear up all your doubts and ensure that we stay transparent about personal information processing.

890700_We will not access, collect, or otherwise process such information, nor will we disclose such information to any third party or use it for any other purpose. This also means that the processing of such information is only performed by you, so it is not subject to this Privacy Notice. If you wish to exercise your rights to such information, or if you wish to modify or delete such information, we will not be able to provide support to you unless you show us how you have processed such information.

889997_Our products and functions include basic and additional functions. By collecting and using your personal information in connection with the basic functions of Photos, we intend to provide you with the basic functions and/or services. You are not obliged to provide the information, but if you do not provide it, in most cases we may not be able to make related services available to you, nor will we be able to respond to or solve the problems you may encounter. You may also not be allowed to use Photos. By collecting and using your personal information in connection with the additional functions, we intend to provide you with more personalized and intelligent Photos services. If you turn on the additional functions, it signifies that you agree to our collection and use of your relevant information. If you do not provide the information, the additional functions may not be available to you. This, however, does not affect your use of the basic functions.
889996_1. The following explains what personal information we collect and use in connection with the basic functions and why we do so:

903701_When you manage your albums locally, the Photos app will need to access your storage data to access, read, or analyze the people, things, or text that appear in your photos or videos, so that you can browse, search for, edit, save, or share the photos or videos in your local albums. Information in connection with this function will be stored on your device only. Local album management includes the following on-device features:
890100_Intelligently classifies and displays your photos and videos.
890098_Enables you to search for photos or videos based on keywords, thus helping you manage your albums more efficiently.
890096_Intelligently creates videos of precious memories based on featured resources.
890095_2. The following explains what personal information we collect and use in connection with the additional functions and why we do so:
890094_(1) Making and restoring photos with AI (only supported by certain devices)

890093_If you wish to make an ID photo or restore your photo using AI, we may request and collect the photo that needs processing. With this information, we will be able to intelligently edit the photo to create the required ID photo or restore the original photo for you. The original photo will be uploaded to the cloud for processing. It will be destroyed immediately after being edited and processed by the cloud server. We will not store your photo or any other personal information on the cloud.
890092_(2) AI-powered color matching (only supported by certain devices)

890091_This function aims to provide you with intelligent photo editing and retouching services. When you use this function for the first time, Photos needs to access your network so that it can download an AI-powered color matcher. When you later use the function to retouch your photos, Photos needs to access your storage data for on-device photo processing.

890089_When you intend to display the location information in a photo or video, if your device is already connected to the Internet, we may request and collect the longitude and latitude values of the photo or video to derive the physical location information and then display it in your photo or video. The longitude and latitude values we collect will be uploaded to the cloud for calculation purposes. They will be deleted immediately after the cloud server figures out the physical location. We will not store longitude and latitude values or other location information on the cloud.
890088_(4) Text scanner (only supported by certain devices)

890087_If your device is connected to the Internet when you use the Text scanner feature, we may request and collect the image that needs processing for higher text accuracy. If we do so, we will upload your photo to our cloud to perform text recognition. If your device is not connected to the Internet, Photos will perform on-device image processing. In the case that your device is connected to the Internet, the image uploaded to the cloud will be destroyed immediately after the cloud server completes text recognition. We will not store any of your personal information, such as your photos, on the cloud.

890085_To provide you with features compatible with your current device and online resource update services, such as downloading algorithmic models and obtaining stickers, music, and other resources, we may need to access your network and collect your device information (DUID, device model, ColorOS version, etc.) and the Photos version and its specific version number to request its background services. The device information already uploaded to the cloud will be destroyed immediately after relevant updates are downloaded. We will not store any of your device information on the cloud.
890084_3. Sharing your personal information with third-party service providers

890083_Some services of the Photos app are provided by third parties. To provide you with such services, we need to provide some of your personal information to these third-party service providers. For example, we may share your personal information with them in the following circumstance:

890081_This service is provided by the Photos app to WeChat. Photos will share with WeChat the people, places, things, and text in your photos or videos, on-device processing techniques (intelligent classification and search techniques), and files in Memories. This is to let you browse files by intelligently classified albums or based on intelligent search suggestions when you intend to share a photo or video via WeChat, thus enabling you to quickly find the required photo or video. The information shared with WeChat will not be uploaded to any server. It is processed on your device only.

890079_When you use the Photos app, we may request certain app permissions to collect and process your personal information and provide you with specific service functions or services. Specifically, we may request the following permissions.

890051_2. How We Retain Your Personal Information

890699_The personal information we collect will be retained for the minimum period needed to fulfill the purposes for which it is collected as described in this Privacy Notice, unless otherwise specified by applicable laws and regulations. Upon the expiration of the retention period or when your personal information can be deleted, we will delete it or process it using special techniques such as differential privacy to ensure that the information will not relate to you.
890021_You can refer to the table below for our information retention and deletion policy.
903700_We do not store your image or video files on our server. You may delete them from your Terminal Equipment at any time.

"903699_When you delete photos and videos from your device's photo library, they are placed in the Recently Deleted album of the Photos app, where they remain for 30 days and then are permanently deleted. You may go to that album to delete them permanently."

890037_3. Our Cooperation with Third-Party Software Development Kit (SDK) Providers

890046_5. Notification and Response to Personal Information Security Events

890045_Please note that although we take reasonable measures to protect your information, no websites, Internet transfers, computer systems, or Wi-Fi connections are 100 percent secure. In the event of any security breach of your personal information, we will, pursuant to applicable laws and regulations, promptly notify you of the particulars and possible impact of such event, the measures taken or to be taken by us, suggestions on how you can prevent and reduce risks, and remedies available to you. We will promptly inform you of the information about such event by email, letter, phone, or push notification. When it is difficult to inform the personal information subjects concerned one by one, we will publish an announcement in a reasonable and effective manner. We will also report the handling of the event in accordance with the requirements of regulatory authorities.

"895460_When you use the \"Shared albums\" feature, we may request and collect your device information (including DUID, device model, ROM version, and region) and your HeyTap Account's token so that you can send an invitation to others, asking them to join the album you shared. To use this feature, you first need to sign up for a HeyTap Account and sign in to it and subscribe to our cloud services. Therefore, to let you use this feature, we have integrated the HeyTap Account SDK into the App. During the account sign-up process, you must read and agree to the Privacy Notice we have developed for the HeyTap Account SDK. The SDK may collect your phone number or email address, account password, and sign-up SMS message to sign you up and assist you in signing in to your account to use related services."
